      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm running a noir-style detective campaign for my friends and I need some help with a plot point. The crime just happened in the West End district—it's one of those older, really neglected parts of the city where the streetlights are always broken, there's a lot of graffiti, and the police barely ever patrol. It's a pretty rough neighborhood with a lot of low-income housing and crowded tenements.\n\nThe victim was found in a dark alleyway behind a liquor store. Based on the vibe of that neighborhood and the setting, what kind of suspect profile should my detective be looking for to make the investigation feel \"realistic\"?",
